6216\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"<project xmlns=\\\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\\\" xmlns:xsi=\\\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\\\" xsi:schemaLocation=\\\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd\\\">\\n  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\\n  <groupId>javax.jcr</groupId>\\n  <artifactId>jcr</artifactId>\\n  <name>Content Repository for Java Technology API</name>\\n  <version>1.0.1</version>\\n  <description>Content Repository for Java technology API.  Specifies a standard API to access content repositories in JavaTM 2 independently of implementation.</description>\\n  <url>http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=170</url>\\n  <licenses>\\n    <license>\\n      <name>Day License</name>\\n      <url>http://www.day.com/maven/jsr170/licenses/day-spec-license.htm</url>\\n    </license>\\n  </licenses>\\n  <inceptionYear>2004</inceptionYear>\\n  <organization>\\n    <name>Day Software Management AG</name>\\n    <url>http://www.day.com/</url>\\n  </organization>\\n  <build>\\n    <plugins>\\n      <plugin>\\n        <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\\n        <configuration>\\n          <source>1.4</source>\\n          <target>1.4</target>\\n        </configuration>\\n      </plugin>\\n    </plugins>\\n  </build>\\n\\n  <distributionManagement>\\n    <downloadUrl>http://www.day.com/site/en/index/related/downloads/RI_download.html</downloadUrl>\\n  </distributionManagement>\\n\\n</project>\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777348555070}]}\n40996:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.4\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 0, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777348555075}}\n41014:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating Gradle repository configuration**\\n\\nI’m considering whether JBoss offers only jar files instead of pom files. It looks like Gradle uses the central pom when it finds a module there and doesn’t check other repositories for artifacts. This prompts me to think about using exclusiveContent or adjusting metadataSources. It seems that once module metadata is found in the first repository, Gradle sticks to that repo for artifact resolution. So, I’ll need to modify settings and potentially use exclusiveContent to prioritize JBoss effectively.\\n\\n**Exploring plugin configurations**\\n\\nI’m thinking that perhaps the plugin uses the central repository first, but maybe exclusiveContent can override that. To test this, I’ll implement it in settings.gradle since the direct build prioritizes settings and showed the central pom. I need to add exclusiveContent before mavenCentral. I’m considering if it’s redundant in build.gradle but could include it there too. I’ll ensure the syntax is valid and might even remove the simple JBoss repo, focusing on settings to avoid conflicts.\\n\\n**Refining repository settings**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the project repositories in build.gradle are still relevant. We could either leave them or align them with exclusiveContent, but I want to avoid confusion and keep things minimal. The root harness compilation only looked at central first, possibly because it was using project repos from build.gradle instead of settings. To play it safe, I’ll apply exclusiveContent in settings, while I may allow the simple repo in build.gradle to stay, but the settings should be the main routing.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0b9ac0062eae00f50169f02fcc186081a1861fa01ebf647bc8\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8C_Vk7e65EaBV9Z14QCzT6ZZr3olIP0SYQaebb7YBiK