{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2569-fails-javac-compile-javax.jcr-jcr-1.0.1-b5ac3bc9\n\nThe most likely failing stage is dependency resolution during `:compileTestJava`, before any real javac source error. In `logs/javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-04-28T03-57-14-079499Z.log` and `build/tests/javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1/b3ed31405eb4a711d268cc79f36b61ad.out`, Gradle fails with `Could not resolve all files for configuration ':testCompileClasspath'` and `Could not find jcr-1.0.1.jar (javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1)` after searching Maven Central only. `logs/javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` also shows the `1.0.1` Maven Central directory has the POM/checksums but not `jcr-1.0.1.jar`.\n\nThe preserved generation log contains a plausible uncommitted fix: add exclusive repository routing for `javax.jcr:jcr` to `https://repository.jboss.org/maven2` in `tests/src/javax.jcr/jcr/1.0.1/build.gradle` and `tests/src/javax.jcr/jcr/1.0.1/settings.gradle`. That matches the per-run outputs in `build/tests/javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1/53ae85dc85a5c2b78372e5195dd5b576.out`, `46c20fd9e0616d9e479727f5de6e3290.out`, and `558d7924d199b1a59c6cc5efc2a6b688.out`, which show the jar resolving from the local Gradle cache and `compileTestJava` / `test` / `nativeTest` succeeding once the artifact is available. Metrics also indicate automation never landed a fix (`iterations: 1`, `generated LOC: 0`, start commit = end commit).\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Recreate/apply the repo-routing change from the preserved generation log so `javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1` resolves from JBoss instead of Maven Central.\n2. Rerun `./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=javax.jcr:jcr:1.0.1 --stacktrace` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javax.j